did my first science project

00:06:40.280 --> 00:06:43.580
because I didn't like
eating my vegetables.

00:06:43.580 --> 00:06:49.010
So a quick show of hands-- how
many of you guys like spinach?

00:06:49.010 --> 00:06:49.780
Whoa.

00:06:49.780 --> 00:06:52.420
How many of you guys
don't like spinach?

00:06:52.420 --> 00:06:53.170
I'm with you guys.

00:06:53.170 --> 00:06:54.950
I'm with you haters.

00:06:54.950 --> 00:06:57.720
So when I was in
third grade, I decided

00:06:57.720 --> 00:07:01.420
that I wanted to make
spinach more exciting to eat,

00:07:01.420 --> 00:07:03.490
so I was going to turn it blue.

00:07:03.490 --> 00:07:04.420
Sounds great, right?

00:07:04.420 --> 00:07:07.830
Blue spinach-- that's
something you'd eat.

00:07:07.830 --> 00:07:11.430
So my parents, bless
their souls, went out,

00:07:11.430 --> 00:07:15.230
bought me a spinach plant,
some blue food coloring,

00:07:15.230 --> 00:07:16.970
and a syringe.

00:07:16.970 --> 00:07:21.440
You should not give a syringe to
a third grader for the record,

00:07:21.440 --> 00:07:23.530
but I took this
blue food coloring,

00:07:23.530 --> 00:07:27.870
and I proceeded to inject
it into the spinach plant,

00:07:27.870 --> 00:07:30.470
and then I forgot about
it for two months.

00:07:30.470 --> 00:07:32.730
And I remember on the
day of this science

00:07:32.730 --> 00:07:37.110
fair I pulled out this dried,
withered, gross spinach

00:07:37.110 --> 00:07:40.690
plant with blotches
of blue on it,

00:07:40.690 --> 00:07:44.780
and I took that in as my
very first science project.

00:07:44.780 --> 00:07:48.030
And I wish I could say
it got better from there,

00:07:48.030 --> 00:07:50.530
but my next project
I literally did

00:07:50.530 --> 00:07:53.620
because I didn't like
taking out the trash.

00:07:53.620 --> 00:07:58.020
In fact, I hated the idea of
rolling that giant garbage can

00:07:58.020 --> 00:08:01.280
to the curb every
