So my tips for the
Google Science Fair

00:32:29.030 --> 00:32:33.260
would be to get your
projects in early.

00:32:33.260 --> 00:32:36.400
So make your
websites before it's

00:32:36.400 --> 00:32:42.190
due in a, week which is what I
did, but seriously actually go

00:32:42.190 --> 00:32:42.690
online.

00:32:42.690 --> 00:32:45.140
Start making your sites
as soon as possible.

00:32:45.140 --> 00:32:48.710
If you have yet to do a
project, start finding mentors,

00:32:48.710 --> 00:32:50.650
ask questions that
matter to you,

00:32:50.650 --> 00:32:52.770
and really follow
the templates that

00:32:52.770 --> 00:32:54.450
are given for the
Google Science Fair

00:32:54.450 --> 00:32:56.590
on how to think through
those questions,

00:32:56.590 --> 00:32:59.990
because they're really a good
starting point if you don't

00:32:59.990 --> 00:33:02.730
know how to go about things yet.

00:33:02.730 --> 00:33:07.100
So those are probably one of the
best tips I can give, actually.

