So [INAUDIBLE], thank you.

00:37:12.380 --> 00:37:16.310
How did you balance school
work with being a scientist?

00:37:16.310 --> 00:37:17.330
And that's hard.

00:37:17.330 --> 00:37:20.920
You know, I did a lot of these
projects during my summers.

00:37:20.920 --> 00:37:23.757
My friends were out
having a good time,

00:37:23.757 --> 00:37:25.590
and we would meet up,
and they would tell me

00:37:25.590 --> 00:37:28.630
about this cool amusement
park they went to

00:37:28.630 --> 00:37:30.131
or the time they
went out to coffee.

00:37:30.131 --> 00:37:32.505
And I'd be like, do you want
to hear about breast cancer,

00:37:32.505 --> 00:37:33.090
though?

00:37:33.090 --> 00:37:33.826
I think you do.

00:37:33.826 --> 00:37:34.540
[LAUGHTER]

00:37:34.540 --> 00:37:39.030
And then I would proceed to
explain my project, but I mean,

00:37:39.030 --> 00:37:40.520
it's a level of balance.

00:37:40.520 --> 00:37:45.030
It really is, and when I was
working as a college student

00:37:45.030 --> 00:37:48.140
I did research while doing
classes at the same time,

00:37:48.140 --> 00:37:50.480
and it ends up being
a juggling act,

00:37:50.480 --> 00:37:54.730
but I will say what
made that possible

00:37:54.730 --> 00:37:59.340
is the fact that I loved every
single thing that I was doing.

00:37:59.340 --> 00:38:01.600
So when I was doing
research and when

00:38:01.600 --> 00:38:04.120
I was doing class work
really late at night,

00:38:04.120 --> 00:38:07.270
it wasn't because I
had to be doing it.

00:38:07.270 --> 00:38:09.710
It was because I
wanted to be, and I

00:38:09.710 --> 00:38:14.170
think if you can find the things
that you love that balance

00:38:14.170 --> 00:38:17.360
becomes so much easier,
but it is a balancing act,

00:38:17.360 --> 00:38:19.530
and it really requires
a level of organization

00:38:19.530 --> 00:38:23.410
that I think you will definitely
develop when you find what you

00:38:23.410 --> 00:38:24.886
love and you're working on it.

