A few more questions.

00:38:38.230 --> 00:38:39.260
This is from anonymous.

00:38:39.260 --> 00:38:43.880
What was the most enjoyable
part of your research?

00:38:43.880 --> 00:38:46.530
Oddly, I've told you
so many experiences

00:38:46.530 --> 00:38:49.060
of messing up in lab.

00:38:49.060 --> 00:38:52.070
I told you about breaking
things, and messing up results,

00:38:52.070 --> 00:38:54.620
and asking questions
that made no sense,

00:38:54.620 --> 00:38:58.500
but I think that my most
enjoyable part of research

00:38:58.500 --> 00:39:03.180
was actually getting results
that made sense I mean,

00:39:03.180 --> 00:39:06.540
I remember there was a moment
in lab where I actually

00:39:06.540 --> 00:39:12.160
got this film-- the result
came out as this film,

00:39:12.160 --> 00:39:14.330
and it just had blobs on it.

00:39:14.330 --> 00:39:16.500
And for anybody else
looking at this result,

00:39:16.500 --> 00:39:17.700
it would make no sense.

00:39:17.700 --> 00:39:21.260
It just looks like
blobs on this film.

00:39:21.260 --> 00:39:23.610
And I remember I
was standing in lab.

00:39:23.610 --> 00:39:26.370
I was looking at it, and one
blob was bigger than the other,

00:39:26.370 --> 00:39:28.250
and that meant something.

00:39:28.250 --> 00:39:30.840
That meant something for
why the cancer cells weren't

00:39:30.840 --> 00:39:34.550
responding, and I was
holding these results,

00:39:34.550 --> 00:39:37.310
and I was thinking
of patients who

00:39:37.310 --> 00:39:40.640
would be impacted by the
results that I was getting.

00:39:40.640 --> 00:39:43.590
And just that feeling of
being able to think through

00:39:43.590 --> 00:39:47.870
from beginning to end and
get something that mattered

00:39:47.870 --> 00:39:51.840
was one of the most powerful
feelings I have ever had.

00:39:51.840 --> 00:39:54.380
And that's been my most
enjoyable part of research,

00:39:54.380 --> 00:39:56.790
and it continues to
be, even many years

00:39:56.790 --> 00:40:00.170
later when I've been doing
research for many more years.

00:40:00.170 --> 00:40:02.130
So if you ever start
research, I hope you--

